    {
      "title": "The Relative Adjective (النسبة)",
      "titleArabic": "النسبة",
      "content": [
        "The relative adjective (النسبة) is formed by adding ـِيّ (-iyy) to a noun to indicate relation, origin, or affiliation.",
        "This suffix creates adjectives meaning 'related to', 'of', or 'from' the original noun."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Add ـِيّ to the noun: مِصْر → مِصْرِيّ (Egyptian)",
        "Feminine form: ـِيَّة (e.g., مِصْرِيَّة)",
        "Remove ta marbuta before adding: مَكَّة → مَكِّيّ",
        "Remove alif/ya at the end: أَمْرِيكَا → أَمْرِيكِيّ"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مِصْرِيٌّ", "english": "Egyptian" },
        { "arabic": "عَرَبِيٌّ", "english": "Arab / Arabic" },
        { "arabic": "إِسْلَامِيٌّ", "english": "Islamic" },
        { "arabic": "يَوْمِيٌّ", "english": "daily" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Special Cases in Nisbah",
      "titleArabic": "حالات خاصة في النسبة",
      "content": [
        "Some nouns have irregular nisbah forms that don't follow the standard rules.",
        "Certain changes occur to accommodate phonetic ease or historical convention."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Nouns ending in ـَاء: صَحْرَاء → صَحْرَاوِيّ (desert-related)",
        "Nouns ending in ـِيّ already: نَبِيّ → نَبَوِيّ (prophetic)",
        "Doubled letters: لُغَة → لُغَوِيّ (linguistic)",
        "Irregular forms: دَم → دَمَوِيّ (bloody)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "صَحْرَاوِيٌّ", "english": "desert-related / Sahrawi" },
        { "arabic": "نَبَوِيٌّ", "english": "prophetic" },
        { "arabic": "لُغَوِيٌّ", "english": "linguistic" },
        { "arabic": "سَمَاوِيٌّ", "english": "heavenly / celestial" }
      ]
    }
